The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, May 06, 2004 				 Panel orders torture probe
																								Calcutta, May 5: The human rights commission today ordered an inquiry into the alleged police torture of Sushil Sharma, a Congress worker.																								Sharmas wife Aparna, a commissioner of Behrampore municipality, had alleged that he was arrested on February 26 in connection with a murder case and tortured in custody. Sharma is known to be close to Adhir Chowdhury, the Congress Lok Sabha candidate from Behrampore.																								The rights panel asked for an additional director-general of police probe into Aparnas charge in which Murshidabad superintendent of police Gyanwant Singh has also been named.
